scope.summary:
GOAL: Implement a theme token system for handshake-native that defines dark and light palettes, supports runtime switching without restart, and provides a muted syntax token set for use in future code editor surfaces. All widgets in MT-002 and all later MTs in WP-KERNEL-011 must consume colors and typography values exclusively from this token system — no hardcoded Color32 values in widget code.

REACT REFERENCE — EXACT TOKENS TO PORT:
  The React app defines tokens as CSS custom properties in app/src/App.css (:root block for light, [data-theme='dark'] block for dark overrides). The native token system must mirror every token defined there:

  LIGHT PALETTE (from App.css :root):
    bg:             #f8fafc
    surface:        #ffffff
    surface_strong: #0f172a
    border:         #e2e8f0
    border_strong:  #1e293b
    text:           #0f172a
    text_subtle:    #475569
    accent:         #2563eb
    accent_soft:    #e0f2fe
    success_bg:     #dcfce7
    success_text:   #166534
    error_bg:       #fee2e2
    error_text:     #b91c1c

  DARK PALETTE (from App.css [data-theme='dark']):
    bg:             #121418
    surface:        #1d232b
    surface_strong: #f8fafc
    border:         #394452
    border_strong:  #d1d5db
    text:           #f8fafc
