    success_text:   #86efac
    error_bg:       rgba(248,113,113,0.2)
    error_text:     #fca5a5

  REACT WorkspaceTheme type (app/src/lib/workspaceSettings.ts line 5): type WorkspaceTheme = 'light' | 'dark'
  The React app also stores custom_theme_tokens: Record<string,string> per workspace settings (workspaceSettings.ts line 12). The native token system must support custom token overrides with the same semantic: a per-workspace override map loaded from the backend settings API and applied on top of the base palette.

SYNTAX TOKEN SET (muted, for code/editor surfaces — not in the React CSS today but needed for MT-011+ code editor panes):
  Derive from the palette. For dark mode:
