EXACT FILES TO CREATE:
  src/frontend/handshake_native/src/theme/mod.rs       (pub mod theme; re-exports)
  src/frontend/handshake_native/src/theme/palette.rs   (HsTheme enum + HsPalette struct + dark/light constructors)
  src/frontend/handshake_native/src/theme/syntax.rs    (HsSyntaxTokens struct)
  src/frontend/handshake_native/src/theme/egui_apply.rs (fn apply_to_ctx(theme: &HsPalette, ctx: &egui::Context))
  tests/native_gui/test_theme.rs                        (unit tests for token values + round-trip)

EXACT FILES TO MODIFY:
  src/frontend/handshake_native/src/app.rs             (add current_theme: HsTheme field to HandshakeApp, call apply_to_ctx each frame, add theme toggle button)
  src/frontend/handshake_native/src/main.rs            (no change needed — app.rs handles theme init)

CORE TYPES:
  // palette.rs
  #[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, PartialEq, Eq, serde::Serialize, serde::Deserialize)]
  pub enum HsTheme { Light, Dark }

  #[derive(Clone, Debug)]
  pub struct HsPalette {
    pub bg: egui::Color32,
    pub surface: egui::Color32,
    pub surface_strong: egui::Color32,
    pub border: egui::Color32,
    pub border_strong: egui::Color32,
    pub text: egui::Color32,
    pub text_subtle: egui::Color32,
    pub accent: egui::Color32,
    pub accent_soft: egui::Color32,
    pub success_bg: egui::Color32,
    pub success_text: egui::Color32,
    pub error_bg: egui::Color32,
    pub error_text: egui::Color32,
    pub syntax: HsSyntaxTokens,
  }

  impl HsPalette {
    pub fn light() -> Self { ... }   // hardcoded Color32 values from light palette above
    pub fn dark() -> Self { ... }    // hardcoded Color32 values from dark palette above
    pub fn with_overrides(mut self, overrides: &std::collections::HashMap<String, String>) -> Self {
      // parse hex strings from overrides map and replace matching fields
      // unknown keys are silently ignored (future-proof)
      self
    }
  }

  impl HsTheme {
    pub fn palette(self) -> HsPalette {
      match self { HsTheme::Light => HsPalette::light(), HsTheme::Dark => HsPalette::dark() }
    }
  }

  // syntax.rs
  #[derive(Clone, Debug)]
  pub struct HsSyntaxTokens {
    pub keyword: egui::Color32,
    pub string: egui::Color32,
    pub comment: egui::Color32,
    pub number: egui::Color32,
    pub type_name: egui::Color32,
    pub punctuation: egui::Color32,
    pub background: egui::Color32,
  }

EGUI APPLY (egui_apply.rs):
  pub fn apply_to_ctx(palette: &HsPalette, ctx: &egui::Context) {
    let mut visuals = if palette_is_dark(palette) { egui::Visuals::dark() } else { egui::Visuals::light() };
    visuals.window_fill = palette.surface;
    visuals.panel_fill = palette.bg;
    visuals.faint_bg_color = palette.surface;
    visuals.extreme_bg_color = palette.bg;
    visuals.hyperlink_color = palette.accent;
    visuals.selection.bg_fill = palette.accent_soft;
    visuals.override_text_color = Some(palette.text);
    visuals.widgets.noninteractive.bg_fill = palette.bg;
    visuals.widgets.noninteractive.fg_stroke = egui::Stroke::new(1.0, palette.text);
    visuals.widgets.inactive.bg_fill = palette.surface;
    visuals.widgets.inactive.fg_stroke = egui::Stroke::new(1.0, palette.text);
    visuals.widgets.active.bg_fill = palette.accent;
    visuals.widgets.active.fg_stroke = egui::Stroke::new(1.0, palette.surface);
    visuals.widgets.hovered.bg_fill = palette.accent_soft;
    visuals.widgets.hovered.fg_stroke = egui::Stroke::new(1.5, palette.accent);
    ctx.set_visuals(visuals);
  }
  fn palette_is_dark(p: &HsPalette) -> bool {
    // heuristic: bg luminance < 0.5
    let [r, g, b, _] = p.bg.to_array();
    let lum = 0.299 * r as f32 + 0.587 * g as f32 + 0.114 * b as f32;
    lum < 128.0
  }

RUNTIME SWITCH IN APP.RS:
  Add to HandshakeApp: current_theme: HsTheme (default: HsTheme::Dark matching the React app's dark default for desktop).
  In update(): call apply_to_ctx(&self.current_theme.palette(), ctx) at the top of every frame.
  Add a theme toggle button in the top bar: label 'Light' / 'Dark'. Button AccessKit: NodeId(10), Role::Button, Action::Click.
  On click: toggle self.current_theme between Light and Dark. The next frame will call apply_to_ctx with the new palette.
  DO NOT persist the theme choice in this MT — persistence via the backend settings API is a later MT concern.

CUSTOM TOKEN OVERRIDES:
  For MT-003, the override map is always empty (loaded from backend in a later MT). The with_overrides() function must exist and be callable; passing an empty map must be a no-op.

HEX PARSING HELPER:
  fn parse_hex_color(hex: &str) -> Option<egui::Color32> {
    // strips leading '#', parses RRGGBB or RRGGBBAA
    let h = hex.trim_start_matches('#');
    match h.len() {
      6 => { let r = u8::from_str_radix(&h[0..2],16).ok()?; ... Some(egui::Color32::from_rgb(r,g,b)) }
      8 => { ... Some(egui::Color32::from_rgba_premultiplied(r,g,b,a)) }
      _ => None
    }
  }
  rgba(...) strings (like accent_soft in dark mode) must be parsed by extracting the r,g,b,a components from the rgba(...) format, NOT hex. Write a small parser for this case.

FONT LOADING (prerequisite unlocked by this MT for later MTs):
  Load Inter font in HandshakeApp::new via cc.egui_ctx.set_fonts(). Font bytes must be embedded at compile time using include_bytes!. For MT-003, embed only Inter-Regular.ttf from assets/fonts/ (to be placed there as part of MT-004 bundling; use a placeholder font path for now or gate font loading behind a cfg feature). If the font file is not found, fall back to eframe default font and log a warning — do not panic.
